A Routine Pair Hand From OKBridge

Pairs is being on the look out at picking up garbage overtricks. Here
is a typical pair type situation.

I am playing OkBridge again after not playing for almost two years.
Not seeing any old partners, I end up in a table scored by match
points.
My partner has a 51% rating and we are playing two players with a 58%
rating.

As South, I held: S Q  H AQ54  D KQJ10  C Q973.
Since my diamonds were so much better than my clubs and since I needed
to prepare for a 1S response by bidding 2C, opening 1D was automatic.

The bidding continued:

West     North      East     South
--            --            --           1D
2D(1)    Dble       Pass      Pass
2H         3H          Pass      3NT
Pass      Pass        Pass

(1)     Majors

The opening lead was the S J

S AK97
H J2
D A542
C 1063

S Q
H AQ54
D KQJ10
C Q973

I won the the lead in my hand and I led a small heart from my hand to
dummy.
LHO thinks about this and generously wins with the heart king and
return a low heart, RHO following to both rounds of hearts.

Now I have ten tricks. Can I reward LHO for his generosity and win 11
tricks? Let's see.
I win two rounds of diamonds in my hand. LHO discards a heart on the
second round.
I play two winning hearts from my hand pitching two small clubs from
dummy.
RHO pitches a club and a spade.
Next I play two diamonds ending on dummy.
LHO pitches a spade, and a club.
I cash the spade ace to which both opponents follow and I pitch a club
from my hand.

S K9
H -
D -
C 10

S -
H -
D -
C Q97

Now I lead a club from dummy. RHO plays the jack and I cover with the
queen.
RHO wins with the club king and returns a low spade.
Naturally, I want to be made a true believer and payoff to LHO leading
the spade jack from jack empty fifth I hook the nine which wins.  LHO
immediately closes the table so his bad result does not count. Now I
remember why I don't play online bridge very often.

This hand was not a difficult one. At the end position, since you knew
LHO started with at least five spades and five hearts, LHO could hold
at most one club. So you have a free shot at making an 11th trick.

