A nicely played hand (and a crappily defended one, I might add).

However, I have an issue with the auction:

West     North      East     South
--            --            --           1D
2D(1)    Dble       Pass      Pass
2H         3H          Pass      3NT
Pass      Pass        Pass

(1)     Majors

The opening lead was the S J

S AK97
H J2
D A542
C 1063

S Q
H AQ54
D KQJ10
C Q973

It is my experience that when two suits have been bid/shown by the
opponents, a qbid shows the one stopped, not the one unstopped.  So in
an unfamiliar partnership, I would have expected North's second call
to be 2S, not 3H.

Perhaps your agreements were different.

Finally (not that it's a big deal), I would think that the seqence
1m-1S-1NT is a better description of your hand than 1D-1S-2C if that
was the sequence you were planning.

I can see opening 1D because the suit is stronger, but those of a pure
KS background would open 1C so as not to preempt us out of clubs when
partner has something like

Jxx
xxx
x
Axxxxx

or the like.

Henrysun909
